   =20
      Everything is securities fraud
   =20
 =20
Every bad thing that a U.S. public company does can be transmuted into secu=
rities fraud: When the news about the bad thing comes out, the stock will d=
rop, and investors will say =E2=80=9Cyou didn=E2=80=99t promptly tell us ab=
out the bad thing, or you didn=E2=80=99t adequately warn us about the risk =
of the bad thing, so we were deceived into buying your stock and have now l=
ost money.=E2=80=9D We  talk about this a lot. It has  some international a=
pplications, but in general, not=C2=A0everything=C2=A0that public companies=
 do outside of the U.S. is securities fraud. The U.S. is very advanced in t=
his matter.But this would be quite a shareholder lawsuit:Geoff Bainbridge, =
the chief executive of [Australian] listed whisky maker Lark Distilling, se=
nsationally quit the company on Wednesday =E2=80=9Cto enable him to manage =
a personal matter=E2=80=9D that was brought to the board=E2=80=99s attentio=
n on Tuesday night.=C2=A0That =E2=80=9Cpersonal matter=E2=80=9D is an alleg=
ed case of international extortion that stemmed from a visit to South East =
Asia well before his appointment as Lark CEO.=E2=80=9CI attended a gatherin=
g with people I didn=E2=80=99t know and don=E2=80=99t remember much more ab=
out that night. However, the next morning I was played footage which made i=
t clear I had been set up as part of a shakedown,=E2=80=9D Bainbridge said =
in a statement.=E2=80=9CFollowing the incident, due to this captured conten=
t I have been the subject of a sophisticated, continuing and recently escal=
ated extortion.=E2=80=9D ...The stock, which had gained 170 per cent in a y=
ear before Wednesday=E2=80=99s announcement, fell as much as 21 per cent in=
 a few hours.Imagine trying to write that risk factor.
