      Where are the customers=E2=80=99 tigers
   =20
 =20
Here are  some words:JPMorgan Chase & Co. has a lounge in the metaverse: Vi=
sitors are greeted by a digital portrait of Jamie Dimon and a roaming tiger=
. Walk upstairs and you=E2=80=99ll see an executive=E2=80=99s presentation =
on the crypto economy.The lounge is located at the Metajuku mall in Decentr=
aland, a browser-based metaverse backed by the Digital Currency Group. Onyx=
, JPMorgan=E2=80=99s blockchain unit formed in 2020, set up the lounge as i=
t released a paper on how businesses can explore opportunities in the metav=
erse.=C2=A0I feel like the tiger is a good idea? If you walk into the offic=
es of an investment bank there=C2=A0should=C2=A0be a roaming tiger to make =
you nervous, keep you on your toes. Obviously in a real bank the tiger woul=
d pose liability problems =E2=80=94=C2=A0it might eat the clients, or the b=
ankers for that matter =E2=80=94 but in the metaverse it is just some nice =
symbolism. =E2=80=9CWe=E2=80=99ve got a really good autocallable accumulato=
r on a basket of NFTs,=E2=80=9D a cartoon avatar of your JPMorgan relations=
hip banker will say, and you=E2=80=99ll almost say =E2=80=9Csure sounds gre=
at I=E2=80=99ll buy $10 million,=E2=80=9D and then the tiger will purr omin=
ously and you=E2=80=99ll tell her you=E2=80=99ll get back to her.
